lace\", \"from\": 1293, \"to\": 1298}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's most famous waterways\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1342}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers will transform this iconic river into the world's largest theatrical stage for what promises to be one of the most spectacular Opening Ceremonies in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1371}, {\"ngram\": \"this iconic river\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1404}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's largest theatrical stage\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1446}, {\"ngram\": \"the most spectacular Opening Ceremonies\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1517}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic history\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1536}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of walking into a stadium, a four-mile-long flotilla of nearly 90 boats will carry athletes from more than 200 countries past hundreds of thousands of spectators seated on the banks of the Seine.\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1735, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0053337747393556e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 1562, \"to\": 1571}, {\"ngram\": \"a four-mile-long flotilla\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1598}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly 90 boats\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1617}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 200 countries\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1666}, {\"ngram\": \"hundreds of thousands\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1707}, {\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1727}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBCU's Opening Ceremony presentation on the Exosphere, which will be simulcast during West Coast primetime coverage between 8:00-11:00 p.m. PT, is expected to include Team USA's and host nation France's boats finishing their journey down the River Seine, passing the Eiffel Tower and Trocadero, as well as the ceremonial lighting of the Olympic cauldron.\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 2097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1743, \"end\": 1747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 1750, \"end\": 1766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9999999998544808, \"rank\": 1.452977390527515e-10, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 1787, \"end\": 1796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exosphere\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0371942045478968e-21, \"text\": \"Exosphere\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exosphere\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exosphere\"}, {\"begin\": 1910, \"end\": 1918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999990127435, \"rank\": 9.833248238119692e-10, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1937, \"end\": 1943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999982529517892, \"rank\": 1.0413529915795714e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1985, \"end\": 1996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\"